bib.title: Single-Particle Structure Of Neutron-Rich Sr Isotopesvia 2H(94,95,96Sr,P) Reactions

free_txt: Data were corrected for beam purity and target deuteron
identified using SHARC array (silicon highly segmented
array for reactions and Coulex) . In downstream
direction at angular range between 35deg and 80deg the
telescope consisted of 140 mu-m thick Strip detector
and 1mm thick unsegmented Si pad detector. At backward
angles between 95 deg and 140deg and between 147deg and
SHARC array was mounted in the centre of
TIGRESS gamma ray detector array. TIGRESS was
composed of 12 HPGe clover deteectors. Each clover
was segmented into 32 segments, which enabled precise
Doppler reconstruction and add-back for reconstruction
The Sr beams were produced by impinging a 480
MeV proton beam on a thick uranium carbide target. Sr
atoms diffusing out of the UCx target were
selectively ionized into a singly charged state using
the TRIUMF Resonant Ionization Laser Ion Source. Sr
ions wre subsequently accelerated in radio-frequency
quadrupole and the superconducting linear accelerator.
